		<Aux:document_text xml:lang="en-US">Quite apart from the essential conversion of motorways, bridges, tunnels, junctions, roundabouts and parking spaces — with the necessary extra costs involved expected to be four times higher than the annual revenue from tolls in Austria — the wear and tear on roads is umpteen times greater than with traditional heavy transporters. Yet giant HGVs are fully authorised in Scandinavia and in some parts of other countries, or tests are being carried out. For the field test in Denmark, which was limited to the motorways, DKK 85 million was provided solely for the reconstruction of roundabouts and junctions, for example. The Commission has merely clarified that the cross-border use of giant HGVs is an infringement of current EC law. 1. Is a revision of the directive regulating the size and weight of HGVs now being planned?</Aux:document_text>
